        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 9:15PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 915 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Manzano Mountain State Park, or 21 miles
southeast of Belen, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mountainair, Manzano Mountain State Park, Manzano, Abo, Tajique
and Torreon.

This includes Highway 60 between Mile Markers 191 and 211.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
